name: Keto Spinach Squares
author: Jason Nicholson
summary: Keto spinach squares. This is a great breakfast recipe for those on a low-carb or keto diet.
ingredients: 2 (10 ounce) packages frozen chopped spinach, thawed and drained
1 (16 ounce) package shredded Monterey Jack cheese
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Place butter in a 9x13-inch baking pan, and put in the oven to melt while preheating
Beat eggs in a medium bowl
Combine flour, baking powder, nutmeg, and salt in another bowl
Add flour mixture to the eggs alternating with the almond milk
Stir in spinach and Monterey Jack cheese
Pour into the melted butter in the baking pan
Bake in the preheated oven until set, 35 to 40 minutes
Remove from the oven and allow to cool for 45 minutes before cutting into 10 squares
